<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-07-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="18" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d18">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7661/1.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-07-19"><hi rend="italic">July 19,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Beaupré states that the Government’s analysis of deviled ham shows a
                            small quantity of boric acid, and that time has been granted for
                            reshipment until an investigation has been made. Says he will send
                            samples.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>